      • logStatusInfo

        void logStatusInfo(UniqueIDInterface log,
                   StatusInterface status,
                   java.lang.String infoID)
        Log a Status Report to a particular log.
        Parameters:
        log - -- the facname of the log to generate the report.
        status - -- the StatusInterface containing the counts to report.
        infoID - -- Name or ID to give to the status information in the log. This is usually used to show the subject of the status info. For example, "Regression Test", "TestCase 123456", etc.. DEFAULT_STATUSINFO_ID used if null or zero-length.
